In the non-linear static time history analysis, it is observed that the structural performance of the bridge varies depending on various factors, including the ground motion. Different ground motions yielded different results, indicating the sensitivity of the bridge's response to different external forces. The highest recorded joint acceleration and displacement are 0.4064 g (3.99 m/s



